Citation.sAbstract: We present densities and dynamic viscosities of binary mixtures of n-octane with ethanol, 1-propanol, 1-butanol, and 1-pentanol. Measurements are performed at atmospheric pressure from (293.15 to 323.15) K using a vibrating-tube densimeter and three Cannon Fenske viscosimeters. We have calculated the excess molar volumes and the viscosity deviations from the experimental measurements. Results have been correlated to Redlich Kister type equations.
Citation.sTitle: Volumetric and Transport Properties of Binary Mixtures of n-Octane + Ethanol, + 1-Propanol, + 1-Butanol, and + 1-Pentanol from (293.15 to 323.15) K at Atmospheric Pressure
